00000000                             1  *******************************************************************************
00000000                             2  * rcMon-68302 v0.3 - sw version (see below)
00000000                             3  *******************************************************************************
00000000                             4  * Written to support my own RCBus 68302 board. Supports simple S-Record loading as
00000000                             5  * well as memory display & modification. No breakpoints, single stepping or
00000000                             6  * disassembly stuff.
00000000                             7  *******************************************************************************
00000000                             8  * This version of the 68302 monitor is the 'sw' version which makes use of the
00000000                             9  * MC68302 internal chip selects to swap ROM and RAM such that RAM is at
00000000                            10  * address 0x000000.
00000000                            11  * 
00000000                            12  * Assumes that an RCBus ROM/RAM v2 board is fitted with:
00000000                            13  *   ROM : 1M organised as 512K x 16bits (2x SST39SF040 FLASH) - BANK 0
00000000                            14  *   RAM : 1M organised as 512K x 16bits (2x AS6C4008) - BANK 1
00000000                            15  *
00000000                            16  * The ROM/RAM v2 board should:
00000000                            17  * + NOT have the 74LS138 and 74LS125 chips fitted.
00000000                            18  * + MUST have the 2 wire links fitted as detailed in the schematic notes.
00000000                            19  *
00000000                            20  * Initially ROM is at address 0x000000 .. 0x0FFFFF (via /CS0)
00000000                            21  *
00000000                            22  * After the switch, ROM is at address 0x600000 .. 0x6FFFFF (via /CS0)
00000000                            23  *              and  RAM is at address 0x000000 .. 0x0FFFFF (via /CS1)
00000000                            24  *
00000000                            25  * Use EASyBIN to split the S-Record into ODD and EVEN bytes.
00000000                            26  * The *_0.BIN file goes in the U ROM socket - holding D08..D15
00000000                            27  * The *_1.BIN file goes in the L ROM socket - holding D00..D07
00000000                            28  *
00000000                            29  *******************************************************************************
00000000                            30  * Exception Handling
00000000                            31  *******************************************************************************
00000000                            32  * After the ROM/RAM switch, the exception vector table is in RAM starting at
00000000                            33  * address 0x000000 and exceptions up to TRAP #15 all have simple handers in ROM
00000000                            34  * that print out a diagnostic message.
00000000                            35  *
00000000                            36  * Some Easy68k TRAP #15 text I/O routines are implemented as follows:
00000000                            37  *   Currently only tasks 0,1,5,6,13 & 14 are supported.
00000000                            38  *
00000000                            39  *******************************************************************************
00000000                            40  
00000000                            41  * TO REDO ************************************************
00000000                            42  * Memory Map
00000000                            43  * 0x000000 .. 0x0FFFFF 1Mb RAM
00000000                            44  * 0x000000 .. 0x0003FF Exception vector table
00000000                            45  * 0x600000 .. 0x6FFFFF 1Mb FLASH
00000000                            46  
00000000                            47  * 008FFF This monitor
00000000                            48  * 0x009000 ..          EhBASIC
00000000                            49  
00000000                            50  *
00000000                            51  * 0xFD0000 .. 0xFDFFFF 64K RCBus MREQ 
00000000                            52  * 0xFE0000 .. 0xFEFFFF 64K RCBus IORQ
00000000                            53  * 0xFFF000 .. 0xFFFFFF MC68302 Internal Peripheral Registers
00000000                            54  *******************************************************************************
